Ken Chenault Net Worth | Celebrity Net Worth           Celebrity Net Worth  Search Random  Ken Chenault Net WorthHow much is Ken Chenault Worth? in Richest Businessmen › CEOsShare on FacebookShare on TwitterRandom CelebrityKen Chenault net worth:$110 Million Ken Chenault Net Worth and salary: Ken Chenault is an American business executive who is the CEO and Chairman of American Express and who has a net worth of $110 million. Ken Chenault was born June 2, 1951in Mineola, New York in Nassau County where he attended he the Waldorf School and received B.A. in history from Bowdoin College in 1973, and J.D. from Harvard Law School in 1976. After Harvard, he worked as an associate at the law firm Rogers & Wells from 1977-1979 and as a consultant for Bain & Company from 1979-1981. He joined American Express in 1981, working in the Strategic Planning Group. In 1995, Ebony magazine listed him as one of 50 living pioneers in the African-American community. He became president and chief operating officer in 1997. He became CEO of American Express in 2001. He is the third African-American CEO of a Fortune 500 company. While CEO of American Express in 2007, Chenault earned a total compensation of $50,126,585, and in 2008, he earned a total compensation of $42,752,461. In 2009, he earned a total compensation of $16,617,639, which included a base salary of $1,201,923, a cash bonus of $10,450,000, an option grant of $3,985,637, and other compensation worth $980,079. He resides in New Rochelle, New York in Westchester County with his wife and children. The Highest Paid CEOs In The World    Kenneth I. ChenaultBusinesspersonDate of BirthJun 2, 1951 (66 years old)NationalityUnited States of AmericaMore CEOs Martin Shkreli Net Worth  Brian Sheth Net Worth  Don Blankenship Net Worth  Peter Szulczewski Net Worth  Apoorva Mehta Net Worth  Dana White Net Worth  Jimmy Iovine Net Worth  Mark Hurd Net Worth  Steve Jobs Net Worth  Marcus Lemonis Net Worth  Share on FacebookAll net worths are ca